      "acceptanceCriteria": "Sensitivity of hemolysis predictions to choice of damage accumulation model (power-law exponent, linear vs. nonlinear) quantified across all operating conditions; alternative model forms evaluated.",
      "rationale": "A single power-law hemolysis model was used without evaluation of alternative model forms or sensitivity to exponent selection. Model-form uncertainty is the dominant unquantified source of error at MRL 5. Flagged as critical epistemic gap; achieved level 1."
